<qti-assessment-item xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0" xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" identifier="Q33_v9" title="Q33_v9" time-dependent="false" adaptive="false" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0 https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/qti/v3p0/schema/xsd/imsqti_asiv3p0_v1p0.xsd">
  <qti-response-declaration identifier="RESPONSE" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier">
    <qti-correct-response>
      <qti-value>ChoiceA</qti-value>
    </qti-correct-response>
  </qti-response-declaration>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="FEEDBACK" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SOLUTION" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SCORE" cardinality="single" base-type="float"><qti-default-value><qti-value>0</qti-value></qti-default-value></qti-outcome-declaration><qti-item-body>
    <p>En una bodega se almacenan tres tipos de cajas. La cantidad de cajas de cada tipo, en función de x (en decenas), es la siguiente:</p>
    <div>
      <table border="1">
        <tr>
          <th>Tipo de caja</th>
          <th>Cantidad de cajas</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Pequeñas</td>
          <td>
            <m:math>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:math>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Medianas</td>
          <td>
            <m:math>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:math>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Grandes</td>
          <td>
            <m:math>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:math>
          </td>
        </tr>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p>Se sabe que la cantidad de cajas medianas es al menos igual a la suma de las cajas pequeñas y las cajas grandes. ¿Cuál de las siguientes inecuaciones representa esta condición?</p>
    <qti-choice-interaction response-identifier="RESPONSE" shuffle="true" max-choices="1">
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceA">
        <m:math>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn>
            </m:mrow>
            <m:mo>≥</m:mo>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>5</m:mn>
            </m:mrow>
          </m:mrow>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceA" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">¡Correcto! La suma de las cajas pequeñas y grandes es (3x + 1) + (4 − x) = 3x + 1 + 4 − x = 2x + 5. Como “al menos igual” significa “mayor o igual que”, la condición se escribe 2x − 3 ≥ 2x + 5.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceB">
        <m:math>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn>
            </m:mrow>
            <m:mo>≥</m:mo>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>5</m:mn>
            </m:mrow>
          </m:mrow>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceB" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. La suma de las cajas pequeñas y grandes no es 4x + 5. Al sumar (3x + 1) + (4 − x) se obtiene 3x + 1 + 4 − x = 2x + 5. Por eso la condición correcta es 2x − 3 ≥ 2x + 5, no 2x − 3 ≥ 4x + 5.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceC">
        <m:math>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn>
            </m:mrow>
            <m:mo>≤</m:mo>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>5</m:mn>
            </m:mrow>
          </m:mrow>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceC" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. La suma del lado derecho sí es 2x + 5, pero “al menos igual” se traduce como ≥, no como ≤. Un contraejemplo es x = 0: esta opción queda −3 ≤ 5, que es verdadera, pero la condición del enunciado sería −3 ≥ 5, que es falsa. Entonces esta inecuación no representa la situación.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceD">
        <m:math>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn>
            </m:mrow>
            <m:mo>≤</m:mo>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>5</m:mn>
            </m:mrow>
          </m:mrow>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceD" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Esta opción falla en dos partes. Primero, la suma de cajas pequeñas y grandes es (3x + 1) + (4 − x) = 2x + 5, no 4x + 5. Segundo, “al menos igual” significa ≥, no ≤. Por ejemplo, con x = 0 esta opción queda −3 ≤ 5, verdadera, pero la condición del enunciado es −3 ≥ 5, falsa.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
    </qti-choice-interaction>
    <qti-feedback-block identifier="show" outcome-identifier="SOLUTION" show-hide="show">
      <qti-content-body>
        <p><strong>Resolución paso a paso</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 1: Identificar cada cantidad</strong></p>
            <p>Cajas pequeñas:</p>
            <m:math>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:math>
            <p>Cajas medianas:</p>
            <m:math>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:math>
            <p>Cajas grandes:</p>
            <m:math>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:math>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 2: Expresar la condición verbal en lenguaje algebraico</strong></p>
            <p>El enunciado dice que la cantidad de cajas medianas es al menos igual a la suma de las cajas pequeñas y las cajas grandes.</p>
            <p>“Al menos igual” significa “mayor o igual que”, es decir:</p>
            <m:math>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mtext>medianas</m:mtext>
                <m:mo>≥</m:mo>
                <m:mtext>pequeñas + grandes</m:mtext>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:math>
            <p>Entonces:</p>
            <m:math>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
                <m:mo>≥</m:mo>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mo>)</m:mo>
                  <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                  <m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>)</m:mo>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:math>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 3: Simplificar la suma del lado derecho</strong></p>
            <m:math>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mo>)</m:mo>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                <m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>)</m:mo>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:math>
            <m:math>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi>
                </m:mrow>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:math>
            <m:math>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>5</m:mn>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:math>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 4: Escribir la inecuación final</strong></p>
            <p>Sustituyendo la suma simplificada:</p>
            <m:math>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
                <m:mo>≥</m:mo>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>5</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:math>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Conclusión</strong></p>
            <p>La inecuación que representa la condición del problema es la alternativa <strong>A</strong>.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </qti-content-body>
    </qti-feedback-block>
  </qti-item-body>
  <qti-response-processing>
    <qti-response-condition>
      <qti-response-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SCORE">
          <qti-base-value base-type="float">1</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else>
    </qti-response-condition>
  </qti-response-processing>
</qti-assessment-item>